reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Drop-in replacement for easy-to-lose stove grommets
reviews.reviewText: Suburban RV stoves have a conveniently removable grate above the burners. A peg on each corner of the grate fits into a hole in each corner of the stovetop. To keep this grate from rattling and hopping out while driving, the holes in the stovetop are equipped with little rubber grommets that just snap into place. They work great, until they disappear like socks in the dryer. Sometimes they can be located by lifting the stovetop and peering underneath. Sometimes not. It's a mystery of RVing where those things disappear to. When all else fails, buy new ones. These replace the factory-issued parts perfectly.
